  %h1 Privacy Policy for IndustryPortal
  %p Last Updated: [Date]
  %p
    Welcome to IndustryPortal, a platform dedicated to providing access to industrial ontologies and semantic artifacts. At IndustryPortal, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our platform.
  %h2 1. Information We Collect
  %p
    %strong Personal Information:
    | When you create an account on IndustryPortal, we may collect personal information such as your name, email address, organization, and other relevant details.
  %p
    %strong Usage Data:
    | We may collect information about how you interact with IndustryPortal, including your browsing activity, search queries, and preferences.
  %p
    %strong Cookies and Similar Technologies:
    | Like many websites, we may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your experience and gather information about your usage patterns.
  %h2 2. How We Use Your Information
  %p
    We may use the information we collect for the following purposes:
  %ul
    %li To provide and maintain IndustryPortal, including account management, authentication, and user support.
    %li To personalize your experience and improve the quality of our services.
    %li To analyze usage patterns and trends, and to optimize the performance and usability of IndustryPortal.
    %li To communicate with you about updates, announcements, and other relevant information related to IndustryPortal.
    %li To comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms of Service.
  %h2 3. Information Sharing and Disclosure
  %p
    We may share your information in the following circumstances:
  %ul
    %li With service providers, contractors, and other third parties who assist us in providing and maintaining IndustryPortal.
    %li With your consent or at your direction, such as when you choose to share information with other users of IndustryPortal.
    %li When required by law or in response to valid legal requests, such as court orders or subpoenas.
    %li In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, where your information may be transferred as part of the transaction.
  %h2 4. Data Security
  %p
    We take reasonable measures to protect your information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  %h2 5. Your Choices and Rights
  %p
    You may have certain rights and choices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of your information. These may include the ability to access, update, or delete your account information, as well as options to manage cookies and tracking technologies. Please contact us if you have any questions or requests regarding your information.
  %h2 6. Updates to this Privacy Policy
  %p
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or applicable laws. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated policy on IndustryPortal or by other means.
  %h2 7. Contact Us
  %p
    If you have any questions, concerns, or complaints regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at [Contact Information].
